data.enText: a list of names or topics that are referred to in a book, etc., usually arranged at the end of a book in alphabetical order or listed in a separate file or book
Look it up in the index.

data.chText: 作者索引和学科索引可在图书馆的数据库中找到。
data.enText: Author and subject indexes are available on a library database.
a system that shows the level of prices and wages, etc. so that they can be compared with those of a previous date

data.chText: 道琼斯指数今天上午下跌了15点。
data.enText: The Dow Jones index fell 15 points this morning.
a sign or measure that sth else can be judged by

data.chText: 新建房屋的数目是国家繁荣的一个有用指标。
data.enText: The number of new houses being built is a good index of a country's prosperity.

data.chText: 指数（如在等式4² = 16中，2是指数）
data.enText: the small number written above a larger number to show how many times that number must be multiplied by itself. In the equation 4² = 16, the number 2 is an index.
to make an index of documents, the contents of a book, etc.; to add sth to a list of this type

data.chText: 所有出版物都按学科和名称编索引。
data.enText: All publications are indexed by subject and title.

data.chText: 将（工资等）与（物价水平等）挂钩；使指数化
data.enText: to link wages, etc. to the level of prices of food, clothing, etc. so that they both increase at the same rate

means: 将(工资等)与(物价水平等)挂钩

ex.chText: 请给我寄一份邮购商品目录。
ex.enText: Please send me a mail order catalogue.

ex.chText: 图书馆有一份所有藏书的目录，按字母顺序排列。
ex.enText: The library has a catalogue of all its books, arranged in alphabetical order.

ex.chText: 请将你方现有目录尽速寄来为盼。
ex.enText: Please rush me your current catalogue.

synonyms.bx: 指商品目录、展品目录或图书馆中的目录。

ex.chText: 我们写信索取一本关于去欧洲度假的宣传手册。
ex.enText: We sent away for a brochure about holidays in Europe.

ex.chText: 其特点在我们的小册子中有详细介绍。
ex.enText: Its features are detailed in our brochure.

synonyms.bx: 指包含产品或服务信息的宣传手册或说明书。

ex.chText: 他们很需要一本新的企业名录。
ex.enText: They really need a new business directory.

ex.chText: 他翻阅电话号码簿找寻她的号码。
ex.enText: He thumbed through the directory to look for her number.

synonyms.bx: 指通常按字母顺序排列的姓名地址录、公司名录、电话簿等。

ex.enText: There is no index at the back of this book.
The index is arranged in alphabetical order.

synonyms.bx: 指书后面列出的可供检索的人名、主题等的列表。

tr: the finger next to the thumb
an alphabetical listing of names and topics along with page numbers where they are discussed
a number or ratio (a value on a scale of measurement) derived from a series of observed facts
can reveal relative changes as a function of time
a mathematical notation indicating the number of times a quantity is multiplied by itself
a numerical scale used to compare variables with one another or with some reference number

example: The government indexes wages and prices

value.boxr_value: The usual plural is indexes, but the form indices can be used for meaning 1. 复数通常为 indexes,但 indices 可以作为义项1的复数形式。

value.def: An index is a system by which changes in the value of something and the rate at which it changes can be recorded, measured, or interpreted.
An index is an alphabetical list that is printed at the back of a book and tells you on which pages important topics are referred to.

example.ex: Curiously, the word 'gay' does not occur in the index...
example.tran: 奇怪的是,gay这个词没有出现在索引当中。

example.ex: There's even a special subject index.

value.def: If you index a book or a collection of information, you make an alphabetical list of the items in it.

example.ex: This vast archive has been indexed and made accessible to researchers...
example.tran: 这个存量巨大的档案室的所有文件都已编了索引,可供研究人员使用。

example.ex: Painters and sculptors are indexed separately...
example.tran: 画家和雕刻家被分开，分别做了索引。

example.ex: She's indexed the book by author, by age, and by illustrator.
example.tran: 她根据作者、年龄和插图画家分别为该书编了索引。

value.def: If a quantity or value is indexed to another, a system is arranged so that it increases or decreases whenever the other one increases or decreases.

example.ex: Minimum pensions and wages are to be indexed to inflation.
example.tran: 最低养老金和最低工资要与通货膨胀挂钩。

value.tran: 使(与…)相应挂钩;使指数化

value.def: If one thing is an index of another, it indicates what the other thing will be like.

example.ex: Weeds are an index to the character of the soil.
example.tran: 杂草是反映土壤特征的一个指标。

value.def: In mathematics, indices are the little numbers that show how many times you must multiply a number by itself. In the equation 32 = 9, the number 2 is an index.
